videos.headline: Wildcats take early lead on TD strike
videos.description: Kentucky QB Stephen Johnson pump fakes and frees WR Blake Bone for a 14-yard TD reception in the back corner of the end zone.

videos.headline: Florida utilizes the wildcat against Kentucky
videos.description: Gators' Kadarius Toney lines up in the wildcat formation and follows his blockers for the 36-yard score to tie the Wildcats 7-7.

videos.headline: Wildcats take lead on Johnson connection
videos.description: Kentucky QB Stephen Johnson throws it high for Garrett Johnson who muscles the catch over the Florida defender to bring Kentucky ahead 14-7.

videos.headline: Kentucky forgets to cover receiver, Gators score easily
videos.description: QB Feleipe Franks finds Tyrie Cleveland who was left uncovered before the snap for a 45-yard score that ties the game at 14-14.

videos.headline: Conrad drags defenders and fights for TD
videos.description: Kentucky takes the lead on Stephen Johnson's third TD pass of the night, this time finding C.J. Conrad over the middle for a 23-yard score.

videos.headline: Communication key for Kentucky in second half
videos.description: Coach Mark Stoops says a breakdown in communication allowed Florida to score easily before the half.

videos.headline: Stingy Kentucky defense forces turnover on downs
videos.description: With the ball at midfield, the Gators were unable to convert on fourth down after the Kentucky defense deflected a pass over the middle. Kentucky takes the ball up 24-14.

videos.headline: Florida finds momentum on reverse-pass
videos.description: A former quarterback, Kadarius Toney takes the pitch and throws it 50 yards to a streaking Tyrie Cleveland on the first play of the drive.

videos.headline: Gators finish creative offensive drive with strong TD run
videos.description: Florida's Brandon Powell takes the direct snap and sprints for the left pylon diving for a score. That Gators trail the Wildcats 27-21 in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: For second time, sleeping Kentucky defense gives up TD
videos.description: The Wildcats' defense leaves Florida's Freddie Swain completely uncovered and give up an easy go-ahead, five-yard score. Florida leads 28-27 as time winds down in the fourth quarter.

videos.headline: Kentucky's missed FG secures Florida's win
videos.description: Kentucky kicker Austin MacGinnis has the line but not the distance and misses the 56-yard field goal as time expires giving Florida its 31st straight win over the Wildcats.

videos.headline: McElwain: Gators didn't give up in stunning win
videos.description: Coach Jim McElwain finds life lessons in his team's effort and fight and credits a tough Kentucky team on a well-played game.

videos.headline: Kentucky suffers heart-breaking loss at the hands of Florida, again
videos.description: Florida's win streak over Kentucky improves to 31 games as critical mistakes and penalties plagued a Kentucky comeback on the final drive.
